neighborhood_overview: Kensington is one of Sydneys oldest suburbs typified by leafy quiet streets and grand federation homes. This part of Kensington is entirely heritage listed because of the architectural significance of the homes. Gertrude and Petunias café is 100m up the road. Kensington Restaurants and cafes are 500m walk. East Sydney Village shopping, bars and restaurants is a 5 minute stroll. The trendy Danks Street coffee shops and the multi-cultural restaurant strip in Kingsford are 20 minutes walk. There is easy, quick access to absolutely everything that Sydney has to offer. The surf beaches of Coogee and Maroubra are 10 minutes drive. Bondi beach is just 20 minutes. The City, the CBD, the Opera House, Circular Quay and the Rocks are 10 minutes by car. The area is full of sporting facilities and recreation areas: The Australian Golf Club, The Lakes Golf club, Bonnie Doon Golf Club are all A-grade courses within 5-10 minutes drive. The SCG, the Sydney Football Stadium, Randwick racecourse and Fox
notes: A comprehensive manual will come with the house so that everything works well for you. We have arranged for the bigger chores to be taken care of (such as pool maintenance, garden maintenance and house cleaning). So you can just enjoy your stay in one of Sydneys best located suburbs.
transit: As a transport hub the position is excellent. 5 Sydney beaches from Bondi to Maroubra are in easy reach. The Opera House is 10 minutes by car. Green Square station is just down the road for trains to the opera house or airport, buses for the city pull up outside the front door and Sydney Airport is 10 minutes away. The M5 motorway, which makes access to the west of Sydney, the Blue Mountains and the rest of New South Wales very convenient, is literally just down the street.

host_about: I am originally from the UK and have been in Sydney for 27 years. We occasionally rent out our home when we are away on holiday ourselves. Most of all the house has been designed for easy outdoor living. We love it. I am sure you will too.

Over the years, we've had various people living with us at our rambling property. And now, thanks to Airbnb, we are sharing the place with the world. space: ABOUT MY FLAT  Relax and chill out in your own private sanctuary - a bedroom complete with a comfortable double bed, mirrored wardrobes, and a gorgeous green leafy outlook. Put your feet up, make yourself at home and enjoy my spacious, light-filled apartment. Inspired by Scandinavian style meets mid-century modern, I've lovingly decorated my living & dining area with a mix of beautifully restored original 1960s pieces and Scandinavian lines.  The sun drenched balcony is my little piece of oasis at home, looking out over a shared garden with stunning big trees. If you are lucky, rainbow lorrikeets might come to visit.  You are also welcome to use the fully equipped kitchen with all appliances, help yourself to an eclectic bookshelf and enjoy all the conveniences of a young professional in Sydney. You will be sharing the shiny modern bathroom with myself.

neighborhood_overview: THE NEIGHBOURHOOD  Waverton is a leafy area within walking distance to Balls Head Reserve, a bushland oasis with stunning views of the Harbour Bridge, City Skyline and Goat Island. Surrounded by greenery, you will be surprised that you are only 10 mins train ride from the city. Waverton Village - 5 mins walk  Quaint village with a supermarket, newsagent, bottle shop, chemist, restaurants, cafes, bakery, hairdresser, drycleaners, health practitioners, Waverton station - everything you need, really! Crows Nest - 15 mins walk  Central shopping village with interesting shops, cosy cafes and loads of restaurants Kirribilli/Milson's Point/Mcmahon's Point  Trendy cafes, pretty tree-lined streets, local pubs, Luna Park, and parks under the Sydney Harbour Bridge pylons - with full frontal views of Sydney Opera House. Catch a scenic ferry ride to Circular Quay, Darling Harbour or Balmain from Milson's Point.
notes: I tend to be out and about, especially during the work week, but generally, I'll go with the flow, and will happily socialise, depending on what works for my guests.
transit: GETTING AROUND  **Walk**  20 mins walk to Sydney Harbour Bridge, where you can take a memorable 1.1km stroll across the Bridge to historic The Rocks and the city  **Train**  5 mins walk to Waverton Train Station  From Waverton Train Station, 3 stops (10mins) to the City  **Bus**  7 mins walk to Pacific Highway bus stop.  From bus stop, 10 mins to the CIty  Easy access to direct buses to Manly & Balmoral Beach Covered car spot available, at additional cost GoGet Cars right on doorstep **To/From Sydney Airport (International & Domestic)**  Taxi: 17km | 30 mins | 60 approx Uber: You can now also catch an Uber from the airport - download the Uber app, and follow the signs at the airport - cheaper than a regular taxi Train: 60 mins door-to-door | 17 one way - you will need to get an Opal card at the train station - follow signs to train station at the airport
access: Of course, you will have access to:  Fresh linen + organic cotton towels  Breakfast cereals, coffee + a huge selection of teas  Unlimited Wi-fi access  Washing machine + laundry detergent  Fully equipped kitchen  Full use of living & dining area  TV, Chromecast, Bose mini speakers Balcony
interaction: As my guest, you are welcome to treat my house as your home away from home - You will have a set keys so that you can come and go as you wish. If you like, I would be delighted to share with you all my nearby favourite spots including secret gardens, little known scenic look outs and the best places for coffee, local lunches, cool bars and yummy desserts.

host_about:
Living in Sydney, while exploring the world

Hi there! I am a professional, living in Sydney for the past 5 years. It's kinda a given - to be on this site - and profess a love for travelling, but it's true! 

Stepping off a plane onto new ground. Seeing new faces, absorbing smells and sounds of different cultures. The unease of exploring unfamiliar territories. Observing similarities & differences of communities across the world. And the taste sensations of food from local kitchens. All these inspire my constant need for seeing new parts of the world, whenever I can. 

And while I'm in between travel, I enjoy exploring my current home city of Sydney - the culture, night life, arts & music scene, beaches and bush. I thought, since I currently have a spare room, why not open my home to fellow travellers?  By making it available on Airbnb, I can continue to meet new people and experience different cultures via the people travelling through Sydney - best of both worlds indeed. 

As my guest, you will be welcome to treat my place as your home away from home, a safe & comfy place to retreat to while you're in Sydney. If you like, I would also be delighted to share little hidden secrets of Sydney that I'm continuing to discover - cool little bars, best local gelato, secret gardens, little known best view points of Sydney skyline and the Harbour Bridge - from around the neighbourhood!

We are long time Airbnb hosts in Paris and now live in a beautiful inner Sydney apartment in the CBD and very accessible to public transport or simply walk.

Your bright  and airy private room has its private bathroom with bath & toilet, an access to the balcony,  a TV with 28 channels and a big dressing and a view on the bay. All linen, towels, - everything you would expect in a hotel but much, much more space at a quarter of the price.

We work during the day and sometimes go out at night but I am sure our paths will cross. We are quiet and very respectful of your space.

The size of the apartment is about 37 square metres. It  is a great apartment, however if you want a big big apartment then this may not be for you.  I own this apartment and it is set up like a hotel room. Everything you need is in there. Iron/h
neighborhood_overview: It is so quiet... there are no busy roads or noise. There are great cafes up at Neutral Bay (Military Road) 10min walk. There is a great little cafe called Thelma and Louise on Hayes Street Neutral Bay. Also, there is a corner store for basic items 2mins walk away There is a bottle shop, newsagent, mini-market at Clarke Road Neutral Bay. Lots of parks by the water and a beautiful harbour path from Neutral Bay to Cremorne Point/Mosman Bay

access: Wi Fi pool car space
interaction: Very little.. Perhaps Meet them on arrival.

Hi there, welcome!

After moving back to Australia a while ago, I found this apartment and love it. I don't live in it, but rather I bought it for other reasons and is available all year round for people to enjoy.

neighborhood_overview: I love the inner city buzz with everyone working in the city during the week & the relaxed serenity on the faces of the happy weekend city day trippers. If you don't mind a little bit of street noise on a Friday/Saturday night, it's very entertaining sitting out on the veranda with a glass of wine watching the young nightclubbers stumbling up & down King Street on their way to the next bar or just trying to stay upright while they're hailing an elusive cab to get home before they pass out on the pavement.
notes: Across the road is a mini supermarket open till late. Next door to that is a great Japanese restaurant. Below in our building is a great little vegetarian Thai restaurant. Around the corner in Sussex St is a 24hr supermarket & 2 blocks up the road on the corner of George St & King St is the Sydney Apple Store, Louis Vuitton Store & a large "Coles Supermarket" which is open until midnight on weeknights & 10pm on weekends. We are surrounded by plenty of nightclubs & great nightlife venues so enjoy the location. We are in the centre of the City and everything Sydney City has to offer is within walking distance. You will save a lot of money from not having to catch Buses, trains & taxis to Sydney's famous tourist attractions.
transit: You can walk to everything so you shouldn't have to rely on public transport other than travelling from the airport which is approximately a 20-25 minute taxi ride or via a short train trip to Wynyard station and a 5 minute walk to the building.  Martin Place & Town Hall train stations are also close by, each about a 6-7 minute walk. You can catch ferries from the King St Wharf to most harbour locations with a 1-2 minute walk to the end of my street. Taxi's are readily available directly outside the building & bus services are readily available from designated stops throughout the city. Walk to Barangaroo, Harbour Bridge, Opera House, Star Casino, Hyde Park, Botanical Gardens, China Town, Centre Point Tower & Darling Harbour.
access: Access is permitted to the entire apartment, except the main bedroom (unless it has been specifically included in your stay). The veranda, rooftop pool & BBQ areas are also accessible.
interaction: I only occasionally sleep at the apartment when one of the rooms are free if I'm there working until late. Other than that I might be around somewhere in the building so I'm easily accessible &  contactable to promptly attend to any requirement you have to ensure your stay is perfect. My goal is for you to feel like you are staying in your own luxury City apartment. I will personally check you in on arrival & ensure you are settled in with all the essentials you need before I leave. You will be able to contact me at all times. You might occasionally see myself or my other guests who will happily assist you with any requests you may have.  Note: This is a 2 bedroom apartment. The other room is also listed. host_about:
I'm a self employed company director. I was born in Sydney and have lived here all my life. I know Sydney like the back of my hand and I'm eager to share my local knowledge of the beautiful places & secret gems Sydney has to offer. I work at the building as the building maintenance manager & I'm around at least half of the time to easily assist you in any way I can. I'm also easily contactable at all other times and I'll ensure I make your stay awesome & memorable.
As a host, I'm always trying to improve and better myself. Every interaction with every guest adds to my experiences as a host & improves my ability to understand and service all of your needs. I love sharing information, life experiences, skills & knowledge and in turn I love to learn from others, hearing new ideas and trying new things. I'm a genuine person, I'm accepting of everyone's unique qualities and differences without any pre-judgement or criticism no matter what it is. I love meeting new people & spending time with family & friends. I enjoy all sports, running on the beach, Surfing, listing to music, going to concerts and movies, travelling and everything else life has to offer. 
I once played competitive sports and with a love for the outdoors I chose to study construction rather than a career that would confine me to an office chair. I also hold an associate diploma in applied science and have traveled extensively throughout Europe, North America & parts of South East Asia. Unfortunately, time & money constraints have prevented more recent travel, although I look forward to travelling more in the near future.

neighborhood_overview: I love the inner city buzz with everyone working in the city during the week & the relaxed serenity on the faces of the happy weekend city day trippers. If you don't mind a little bit of street noise on a Friday/Saturday night, it's very entertaining sitting out on the veranda with a glass of wine watching the young nightclubbers stumbling up & down King Street on their way to the next bar or just trying to stay upright while they're hailing an elusive cab to get home before they pass out on the pavement.
notes: Across the road is a mini supermarket open till late. Next door to that is a great Japanese restaurant. Below in our building is a great little vegetarian Thai restaurant. Around the corner in Sussex St is a 24hr supermarket & 2 blocks up the road on the corner of George St & King St is the Sydney Apple Store, Louis Vuitton Store & a large "Coles Supermarket" which is open until midnight on weeknights & 10pm on weekends. We are surrounded by plenty of nightclubs & great nightlife venues so enjoy the location. We are in the centre of the City and everything Sydney City has to offer is within walking distance. You will save a lot of money from not having to catch Buses, trains & taxis to Sydney's famous tourist attractions.
transit: You can walk to everything so you shouldn't have to rely on public transport other than travelling from the airport which is approximately a 20-25 minute taxi ride or via a short train trip to Wynyard station and a 5 minute walk to the building.  Martin Place & Town Hall train stations are also close by, each about a 6-7 minute walk. You can catch ferries from the King St Wharf to most harbour locations with a 1-2 minute walk to the end of my street. Taxi's are readily available directly outside the building & bus services are readily available from designated stops throughout the city. Walk to Barangaroo, Harbour Bridge, Opera House, Star Casino, Hyde Park, Botanical Gardens, China Town, Centre Point Tower & Darling Harbour.
access: Access is permitted to the entire apartment, except the second bedroom (unless it has been specifically included in your stay). The veranda, rooftop pool & BBQ areas are also accessible.
interaction: I only occasionally sleep at the apartment when I have a booking as I try to keep it to a minimum if possible, to give you maximum privacy during your stay. I work several days a week at the building as the building manager & maintenance provider which is when I occasionally stay. Other than that I might be around somewhere in the building making me easily accessible &  contactable & will promptly attend to any requirement you have to ensure you have the perfect stay. My goal is for you to feel like you are staying in your own luxury City apartment. I will personally check you in on arrival & ensure you are settled in with all the essentials you need before I leave. You will be able to contact me at all times. You might occasionally see myself or a roommate who will happily assist you with any requests you may have. (Note: I currently don't have a roommate in the second room. It is not my main residence so I only stay there 1-2 nights a week although this can change at any time).
house_rules: Arrival: please verify expected arrival time a minimum 48hrs prior to your arrival to ensure you are not kept waiting when you arrive for your booking. I do not live at the building & I arrive in advance of meeting you for check-in to prepare the apartment for you so at times you may have to wait for the preparation to be 100% complete.  Cleaning: The apartment is self-serviced, cleaning equipment is provided. A one off 'departure clean' fee is charged at the time of making the booking. Additional cleaning can be arranged by request at a small additional cost. Fresh linen, bedsheets & towels etc are provided for self service. If possible, and time permits, please wash & dry your used, linen, towels, sheets etc & return them to the linen shelf. Sufficient washing powder is provided to allow for linen self washing. Rubbish can be emptied into the rubbish chute accessible from the lift lobby directly outside the apartment door. Enjoy your stay. Respect the apartment, myself & any roommate
host_about:
I'm a self employed company director. I was born in Sydney and have lived here all my life. I know Sydney like the back of my hand and I'm eager to share my local knowledge of the beautiful places & secret gems Sydney has to offer. I work at the building as the building maintenance manager & I'm around at least half of the time to easily assist you in any way I can. I'm also easily contactable at all other times and I'll ensure I make your stay awesome & memorable.
As a host, I'm always trying to improve and better myself. Every interaction with every guest adds to my experiences as a host & improves my ability to understand and service all of your needs. I love sharing information, life experiences, skills & knowledge and in turn I love to learn from others, hearing new ideas and trying new things. I'm a genuine person, I'm accepting of everyone's unique qualities and differences without any pre-judgement or criticism no matter what it is. I love meeting new people & spending time with family & friends. I enjoy all sports, running on the beach, Surfing, listing to music, going to concerts and movies, travelling and everything else life has to offer. 
I once played competitive sports and with a love for the outdoors I chose to study construction rather than a career that would confine me to an office chair. I also hold an associate diploma in applied science and have traveled extensively throughout Europe, North America & parts of South East Asia. Unfortunately, time & money constraints have prevented more recent travel, although I look forward to travelling more in the near future.

Whilst the apartment borders Darling Harbour and Chinatown you will have the touch choices of many varieties of Restaurants. Walk 150 metres to the left takes you to the main street of Sydney (George Street) and World Square. To the left of the building, the rooftop overlooks the whole of Darling Harbour and Chinatown Gardens and the newly constructed Exhibition Centres to the beautiful waterways of Darling Harbour into Sydney Harbour. Diagonally located to the apartment is the demolished site of the Sydney Entertainment Centre. It's virtually central to everywhere in the city of Sydney.

neighborhood_overview: Erskineville has a history that is connected to the railways, and also manufacturing (including boots and bolts). More recently the area has been undergoing transformation, and we now have a vibrant and diverse neighbourhood. We have lived here for 20 years and our children have grown up here and attend local schools. We have always felt there is a sense of community. The local village strip is a short stroll, with traditional pubs, small bars, cafes, restaurants, a deli, bakery, chemist, newsagency, post office, vet, florist, petrol station, and a more recent small supermarket. Many nearby parks, ranging from pocket parks and playgrounds, and doggie parks, an oval, and bowling greens; so there is plenty of choice if you like to get outside to play, or run, or socialise...or bowl. From Erskineville is an easy walk to the buzz and lively activity along King Street and Enmore Road. Also in easy walking distance there is Carriageworks (for a range of events including the Saturday morning
notes: We may require a  5 night minimum stay over peak holiday periods. We provide beds and towels for each guest as per the reservation request. We aim to be accomodating and flexible. Additional guests may only stay with prior agreement, so please ensure to ask beforehand (no couchsurfers). The extra person fee applies for each additional guest, for each night of the reservation. Additional guests staying shorter periods is 55/night. Discount rates after 7 nights & discounts for children up to 10 years, so please let us know. A travel cot is available for babies, or a cot mattress (no charge for babies). Wifi is available in the rear living area. Cleaning fee does not include washing dirty dishes. We can offer a reduced cleaning fee for bookings of 1 or 2 guests (single or couple). Our water is supplied by Sydney Water & they guarantee it is 100% filtered and safe to drink straight from the tap (you do not need to buy bottled water). Pets may be allowed by prior agreement.
transit: Ersklneville is between 2 major railway lines, the Western line (Macdonaldtown and Newtown stations), and the Southern Line (Erskineville station). Both lines take you to the city (10 minutes), including Circular Quay (14 minutes) where you can connect with ferries to destinations across and around Sydney harbour (including Taronga Zoo and Manly). An easy walk to King Street and many bus connections, including the 370 to Coogee beach. In walking distance is the heritage listed Carriageworks . Sydney Uni and the RPA hospital are also easy to reach by walking (approx. 2km & 1km). The domestic and international airports are on the train line, and by taxi approx. 20 minutes. With your own vehicle, parking in the area is predominantly on street, and there is a mix of restricted and unlimited parking in the surrounding streets.

interaction: We are happy to be of assistance if requested

Please consider if the bedding availability as described suits you. There is some room for flexibility and we can discuss, but we do not allow the furniture to be dragged around.

We have lived in Erskineville for just over 20 years and brought up our family in this neighbourhood. We are community minded and enjoy being involved in community efforts. We care about our environment and consciously try to reduce waste, minimise consumption and support local. We enjoy travelling, cycling, camping, water activities, good food, good coffee, getting together with friends and family. Myself I like art and crafts, working with my hands, designing and design. neighborhood_overview: This place really is a unique opportunity to live like a Sydney-sider. Spring is the perfect time to visit Sydney and the city is the place to be. With festivals and shows popping up all over the city including Hyde Park and the Rocks and with weekend markets just a short walk into Surry Hills and Paddington, this place is perfected located for discovering Sydney. Mrs Maquiarie's Chair is a lovely 5km round trip (40min walk) and the Sydney Opera House is only a 30min walk through the city. Amazing cafes are just across the road in Surry Hills with 5-10min walks to gems like Paramount Coffee Project, Reuben Hills and Single Origin Coffee Roasters. My personal recommendation is Suzie Q Coffee which is about a 15min walk into Surry Hills. The nightlife is buzzing this side of town with hidden bars and amazing restaurants in Surry Hills, cheap eats down George St and China Town and clubs in the city. The closest supermarket is the IGA on Oxford St or Coles in World Square, both about 5min
transit: Museum train station is literally across the road making it super fast and easy to get to from the airport and buses are just down the road. Central station is a 10min walk away and the train will get you anywhere you need to be in Sydney. The apartment is also next door to the Travelodge so there is always a taxi outside as any time of the day or night.
access: The apartment is on the 9th floor and the building has a lift. The space is secure with a swipe to enter the building and swipe access to the 9th floor and rooftop only. The rooftop located on the 20th floor has a lap pool, barbecue and entertaining area and a glimpse of the Sydney Opera House.
interaction: My husband and I will be overseas during your stay however in case of emergencies, we will leave a contact number for you to call should you require any help.
house_rules: This apartment is my family home and I have built a life in this lovely space. I have my precious belongings in this house which I have collected over the years and would just ask that you respect and appreciate my house as such. I encourage you to take advantage of my home and would hope that you treat it as though it is your own. I understand that things may get damaged so please just let me know so that I can repair them or have them replaced.
host_about: My name's Julie. I grew up in Melbourne and I currently live in Sydney Australia. I love sport, coffee, food and friends. I enjoy meeting new people and travelling around if I have time, but mostly I don't so eating out, cooking and bumming around watching TV are favourite pastimes of mine.

name: Waterfront Postcard
summary: Cosy apartment on Sydney's waterfront with a view from the garden of the Opera House and the Harbour Bridge! Your private bedroom has its own balcony over a quiet and leafy cul-de-sac street. Central location. Excellent transport and local amenities.
space: Welcome to my B&B! I live here on Sydney Harbour and offer you a private room in my apartment with a queen-size bed. The room comfortably fits a couple and is same-sex friendly.   Sit in the private garden downstairs with a book or a bottle of wine and enjoy the postcard view of the Opera House and the Harbour Bridge.    The five-minute ferry ride across the harbour to Circular Quay, the Opera House and the historic Rocks district is a mere 15-minute walk away. Or walk across the famous bridge into the heart of The Rocks in 40 minutes. Wherever you need to go, be it Bondi Beach, the Bridge Climb or Taronga Zoo, you can get there inside an hour. My location is ideal for visitors to Sydney.   All towels and linen are provided.
description: Cosy apartment on Sydney's waterfront with a view from the garden of the Opera House and the Harbour Bridge! Your private bedroom has its own balcony over a quiet and leafy cul-de-sac street. Central location. Excellent transport and local amenities. Welcome to my B&B! I live here on Sydney Harbour and offer you a private room in my apartment with a queen-size bed. The room comfortably fits a couple and is same-sex friendly.   Sit in the private garden downstairs with a book or a bottle of wine and enjoy the postcard view of the Opera House and the Harbour Bridge.    The five-minute ferry ride across the harbour to Circular Quay, the Opera House and the historic Rocks district is a mere 15-minute walk away. Or walk across the famous bridge into the heart of The Rocks in 40 minutes. Wherever you need to go, be it Bondi Beach, the Bridge Climb or Taronga Zoo, you can get there inside an hour. My location is ideal for visitors to Sydney.   All towels and linen are provided. · B A L C O N
neighborhood_overview: Those iconic photos of Sydney Harbour, stretching from the bridge to the Opera House, are taken from my neighbourhood: Kirribilli. Leafy, green, peaceful and safe, Kirribilli is quiet but active with the sounds of Australian life carrying across the water.    In November the jacarandas which line the streets pop with lilac-coloured flowers. In summer, fireworks regularly burst over the harbour—my backyard. The place is so nice, the Prime Minister of Australia lives a few doors away. Fair dinkum.   Kirribilli is eminently walkable, but it is hilly and steps are common. The village is uphill of me but the hill is gradual. As I live on the water, there are no hills at all between me and the ferry wharf.   Amenities here are excellent—transport, cafes, groceries, laundry, cashpoint/ATM and post office are all within a 15-minute walk.
notes: • CHECK-IN & CHECK-OUT TIMES   I'm quite flexible with times, but if I have back-to-back bookings I will need to insist on a 2pm check-in and a 12 noon check-out to give me time between guests to clean your room. Nevertheless, I realise we travellers are often at the whim of the airlines, so I'm not a tyrant about it. We can always work something out.   • N O I S E   My space caters to quiet singles or couples. I am a quiet person who likes a peaceful home, and when I am writing I need it. Please be respectfully quiet for my neighbours, too; inside the building the large atrium echoes, and outside sound travels easily on my quiet street (as passing drunks sometimes demonstrate in summer). Please keep your voice down if you are on the balcony at night.   On balance I live in a quiet area, especially given my close proximity to the city. On summer weekends, passing party boats on the water can be a little annoying with their music, and it isn't unusual for there to be a house party in ea
transit: The local train station and two ferry wharves are all within 15 minutes walk and will get you from your room to the city centre (Circular Quay or Central Station) within half an hour. You can even walk it across the Harbour Bridge in 40 minutes.   Public transit is excellent, but parking is not. There is on-street parking only, and when events are on it can be competitive. I can supply a guest permit for exemption from normal parking time limits.   Door-to-door on a smooth journey, I am 45 minutes from the airport. You can choose to:   • go cheapest: catch the train to Central Station, change to the T1 line and travel three stops to Milsons Point. Walk here (10-15 mins). Total travel time 45 mins, cost ~17pp. Or:   • go scenic: catch the train to Circular Quay and catch a ferry across the picturesque harbour (welcome to Sydney!) to either Kirribilli wharf or Milsons Point wharf. Walk here (10-15 mins). Total travel time 45 mins, cost ~23pp. Or:   • go direct: catch a taxi from the ai
access: · B A L C O N Y   The room has a private balcony suitable for smokers, for a bottle of wine, or for reading a book. PLEASE NOTE that the balcony does NOT face the water but has a peaceful leafy suburban outlook.    I live three storeys above ground level (and my building has a lift).   · WATERFRONT GARDEN   The building has a private garden for residents and guests with seating on absolute waterfront—step any closer to admire the sweeping view from the Opera House to the Harbour Bridge and you'll get wet.   · B A T H R O O M   The bathroom is shared, but please don't worry about making it available to me. Use it like you own it! I am very flexible and I want you to be comfortable.   Basic toiletries, hairdryer, towels and washcloths are supplied.   · K I T C H E N   The kitchen is not shared but you can store things in the fridge and use the sink. Guests may not prepare meals, but there are many local cafes and restaurants.   · LIFT (ELEVATOR)   I live on the top floor, but there is a
interaction: You will have one room in a two-bedroom apartment; the other is mine, but your privacy is yours. I am quiet and discreet and you won't much notice me as I am often working at the computer in my room.   As a freelance writer I work from home and need reasonable quiet. However, I am affable and happy to talk, and am always available to answer your questions. I am home most of the time.
house_rules: I have a few simple rules. Please respect me and my home by adhering to them:   • NO VISITORS    · Please do not invite visitors into the apartment. I work from home so it is also my office, and unknown visitors are disruptive to my work routine. If you are meeting someone please arrange to meet them outside.   · Please do not take visitors into the garden. Building management does not allow this.   • W O O D   Please use a coaster. Don't put any drinking glasses, hot mugs or cold bottles, nor any wet towels, on any wooden furniture. I have some modest pieces of unvarnished, oiled wood furniture I have lovingly collected over the years, and water stains are painful scars.   • SMOKING    · Smoking on balcony only.  · Smoking is not permitted in the garden.   • AND FINALLY...    · Kitchen is not shared.  · Please remove your shoes inside.
host_about:
As a freelance travel writer (search for Solonaut) I am a seasoned traveller and understand travellers' needs. I love travelling as a mid-budget backpacker and have been to countless places around the world. I have a great deal of lodging experience. I am also an AirBnB host when I am at home in Sydney.

Canadian-born, I've tallied twenty-plus years in Sydney and know it well. I can help you with visitor information and local travel tips.

At home I like peace and quiet, and when I am working at home I need it.

As a guest lodging elsewhere, I am typically out all day exploring, shooting and writing, and I usually only return to my lodging to sleep.

name: Beautiful apartment, idealic location
summary: A beautiful and tastefully decorated, well-appointed room in a stunning two-bedroom apartment in the heart of the Sydney CBD and nestled on the harbour.  Darling Harbour and the acclaimed Sydney ferry service are on your  doorstep - a celebrated tourist and entertainment precinct, located within walking distance from Sydney's iconic destinations, including intimate bars and cafes, all transport and shopping paradise.  Private bathroom, beautiful bedroom and everything scrupulously clean.
space: You will have the benefit of a very comfortable queen size bed, access to plenty of wardrobe / closet space, your own bathroom, and a beautifully furnished living and dining room with Netflix, Stan, free-to-air TV and unlimited WiFi.

Darling Harbour and the acclaimed Sydney ferry service are on your  doorstep - a celebrated tourist and entertainment precinct, located within walking distance from Sydney's iconic destinations, including intimate bars and cafes, all transport and shopping paradise.  Private bathroom, beautiful bedroom and everything scrupulously clean. You will have the benefit of a very comfortable queen size bed, access to plenty of wardrobe / closet space, your own bathroom, and a beautifully furnished living and dining room with Netflix, Stan, free-to-air TV and unlimited WiFi. There is no cooking other than using the toaster for your toast each morning.  Cold water is on hand at all times. You will have access to the balcony with water glimpses and a lovely cityscape view. There is an internal laundry with washing and drying facilities - in your
neighborhood_overview: Steps from the King Street Wharf entertainment precinct, moments from Darling Harbour, down the street from Barangaroo - the largest urban renewal project in Sydney's history - and an easy walk to any point in the CBD, you will be staying within easy reach of Sydney's dining, entertainment, and drinking venues.  You will be near the harbour and in an entertainment area, therefore there is some noise, from traffic and people. When windows and doors are shut there is virtually no noise. However if you like to sleep with your window open there is traffic noise, we do provide ear plugs if you are from a remote area and noise sensitive. People who are city dwellers and global travellers claim there is no noise.
notes: The front door requires manual locking on both exiting and after entering the apartment. A swipe is required for you to enter the front of the building and then again in the elevator to gain access to the apartment floor.
transit: You will have the benefit of easy access to public transport to any point in Sydney. Purchase an Opal card (at any corner store, news agency or at the airport) - Sydney's touch-on touch-off integrated ticketing solution.  If you are flying into Sydney Airport, your room is a 21-24 min train ride (running every 9 mins during peak hours) and a quick 3 block walk away.  If you want to lap up the sun at Bondi, you'll be a 45 min bus ride away.  Taronga Zoo is a pleasant stroll to Circular Quay and a 12 min ferry ride away.  These are just some examples, but hopefully you get the idea!
access: There is no cooking other than using the toaster for your toast each morning.  Cold water is on hand at all times. You will have access to the balcony with water glimpses and a lovely cityscape view. There is an internal laundry with washing and drying facilities - in your bathroom which you may use. Please leave all doors open when using the dryer. Ironing facilities are also available.
interaction: The benefits of inner-city living and and being located on the harbour are enormous, and I am more than willing to share some insights, tips and recommendations of places to go, eat, and drink. You will be able to walk everywhere, or catch a ferry - the terminal is 2 minutes from your doorstep. I work from home on occasions, so may not always be able to chat even if I am home.  That said, it goes without saying that I'm more than happy to do my best to help out with any challenges you may face during your time in Sydney.
house_rules: Smoking is not permitted. No pets allowed. No parties allowed. No guests allowed. There are many quirky small bars and numerous streets filled with restaurants and entertainment at your doorstep. You should also aim to keep the living room - a shared space - in the same state as you find it : that is, tidy. Feet with shoes on are not to be placed on the furniture, feet with socks absolutely permitted.  Please place glasses/cups that you are using onto drink coasters provided. If using your laptop on the dining table always use the placemat provided.
host_about: I am a Director of a small company, with a reasonably busy work schedule. My home is my castle, therefore really would prefer professional or corporate  guests who appreciate fine furnishings and a beautiful space. I love living in the hub of Sydney, on the water - close to wine bars, cafes and a short stroll into the city. I enjoy theatre, art house cinema, galleries, exhibitions, good wine and  food. My guests have told me my home is five star accommodation.

neighborhood_overview: Darlinghurst is a vibrant inner-city suburb rich with history and bustling with contemporary diners, bars, shops and restaurants. Oxford Street delivers a lively pulse to this colourful area. Starting from the city, this iconic street moves from a commercial hub to a longer stretch of boutique and bar offerings as you progress east. Nearby Crown, Victoria and Liverpool streets are also lined with trendy boutiques, cafes, bars and restaurants. Just off Oxford Street on Burton is the teeny tiny Pocket Bar, a friendly loungeroom-like bar serving good eats and great cocktails. At old-school American joint Jazz City BBQ on Crown Street you can grab yourself a killer burger, malted milkshake, sweet potato fries or even classic american bbq. There's also the boundary-pushing Cafe Paci on Riley Street, sure to impress with their avant-garde fusion fare. It's at night that Darlinghurst really comes alive as the area's network of clubs, pubs, performance venues, small bars and gay bars fill up.
notes: We have a female cat (Indie) who will occasionally be staying at the residence while guests are there. If she is there she will need to be fed and kept inside. Other than that, she is great company and you will need to be a cat lover. If you'd prefer to not have Indie stay we can arrange for her to visit cat camp.
transit: Aside from exploring on foot, the best way to travel to Darlinghurst from the city is by bus. There are handy buses running between Sydney City and along the concourse of Oxford Street to Bondi Junction, from early in the morning until late into the night. The apartment is a 10 minute walk to Kings Cross Train Station. 5-10 minute walk to multiple bus stops. 20 minute walk to the CBD.

interaction: We live here so if the place is available it usually means we are away, however we will make ourselves very easily contactable via phone, email etc. We are happy to help with any recommendations for things to do and places to visit in and around Sydney.

neighborhood_overview: Bondi Beach is one of Australia's most famous beaches and among the world's most well-known beaches. The beach is roughly a kilometre long and is patrolled by lifesavers who make swimmers stay between the yellow and red flags. At any time of the year, Bondi Beach is a buzzing morning, late afternoon and night-time scene. Enjoy a tasty coffee and some breakfast before walking the Bondi to Coogee coastline. Take in a long, lazy lunch in one of the suburb’s excellent restaurants. Among the dining options is Sean’s Panaroma, a landmark of Bondi culture. It offers a mix of classic Italian and Australian dishes as well as superb views of the beach and ocean. At the other end of the beach, you’ll find Icebergs Dining Room and Bar, with its stunning views. Join the queue at Gelato Messina - it will give you time to make your choice from the daily ice cream specials board. Finish a perfect day in Bondi with a cocktail as you rub shoulders with popular Sydney stars who call this beachside icon h
notes: Please note, there is NO off street parking at this premises.
transit: Buses galore from Bondi beach.  Express bus (333) to the city takes approx 20 mins. Uber is popular Sydney and it's great way to get around. Take an Uber to Rose Bay Wharf or just walk there (20min), then catch a Sydney ferry into Circular Quay, right next to the Opera House and Harbour Bridge.

neighborhood_overview: Impressive and extremely convenient surroundings. We're situated on Kent St in Sydney's CBD, just a stone's throw away from Darling Harbour and Wynyard Station. There’s really nowhere in the world quite like Darling Harbour. From first light to starry nights, there’s always something going on here. Coffee machines froth, water laps, children play, friends chat, steaks sear, glasses clink, bass thumps and fireworks crackle. Infectious sounds travel on harbour breezes as text messages and online updates share snapshots of good times. There are tons of things to do in the city itself which are mostly a quick stroll away. I've included most of my favorite places and more in my extensive "Local Recommendations Guidebook" on this listings page, so please feel free to check em' out for awesome things to do and eat in the CBD area.

neighborhood_overview: Bondi has come a long way in the past couple of years, from a haven for tourists that enjoy a nice view and surfies who like to ride a decent wave, to a metropolitan hotspot with great restaurants, bars and café's.  We even have a Messina Gelato a dangerous ten minute walk from the house!! In case you're unfamiliar with Messina, they most recently won the gold crown in the Gelato World Tour. There is so much to do and see and I am more than happy to supply suggestions to my visiting guests!
notes: Please note that the apartment is on the top floor - this means there are a number of stairs, four short flights of them. If this is a concern for you please contact me, I am happy to have a chat about whether I think it is a good idea to book. There is NO lift.
transit: Located across the road from Public Transport. Most buses if not all head to Bondi Junction- the main hub for buses and trains in the Eastern Suburbs.   From the airport you will need to jump on a train to Central Station. Platform 25 at Central will take you to Bondi Junction and then a you will need either the 380 or the 333 to Bondi Beach.  Note: you will need an Opal Card - you can get them free card from most convenience stores or the ticket vending machine at the station. You just need to top these cards up, you can use the Opal card on all public transport When getting out of Bondi it is better to get the bus from Hall Street location as the closest bus stop gets ridiculously busy at the end of a hot summers day. Uber is the best option for ride shares - just download the app, and follow the instructions,  Taxi's all have meters and are easy to hail off the street.
access: The space is open and guest will have access to everything around the place.
interaction: I will be away but if guests have any issues my Brother is around the corner and can assist if necessary.
house_rules: No parties please. This is a Unit block with permanent residents that work Monday - Friday. We need to respect them as they respect our guests
host_about:
Hi All! 
So I am no long and an airbnb newby, over the last 18 months I have hosted 104 people from over 50 different countries. With so many different people there has been some interesting moments, lots of wine, some cheese and way too much Chilean pisco. 

Airbnb has been a great experience, it has been wonderful sharing my home with so many different people. 

You want to know a bit about me? I am a fun, friendly, easy-going, local girl that would love to share some of the relaxed Bondi life with some new mates (like you). In the summer, I can be found on the beach or doing yoga, occasionally I even break out the old sneakers and do the cliff run. My favorite thing is a cheeky glass of wine on a Sunday afternoon watching the sun set over Bondi -  especially when there is a bit of cheese and some good company to go with it! 

I've lived in Bondi for nearly 5 years now (it’s gone by FAST).  People often ask me what it’s like to live in such a beautiful spot. It’s simple really – it’s bloody awesome! There is nothing like going for a swim in the ocean before work…that is if I can get myself to leave the sun soaked coziness of my living room.

I have done lots of travel myself and understand the need to find that great little spot that only the locals know about. This is the biggest reason I love Airbnb, it makes travel so much more personal and allows everyone to get the ‘local experience’.  I’m really pleased at the prospect of playing a part in someone’s dream holiday!

Come on over and give me the chance to enhance your Bondi experience! I’m pretty enthusiastic about our little part of the world so always happy to give advice or point you in the right direction!

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located at the intersection of the Sydney CBD, Darlinghurst, and Surrey Hills.... it's an AWESOME place to stay!  You can walk pretty much everywhere from the apartment including: Harbour Bridge, Opera House, Sydney Harbour, Botanical Gardens, Sydney CBD and shopping arcades, Funky suburbs such as Surrey Hills/ Potts Point/ Paddington, Contemporary Arts Museum, National Gallery, NSW State Museum, China Town, Darling Harbour, Rushcutters Bay...... all within a 20min walk. Darlinghurst and Surry Hills is famous for great cafes, small bars, amazing restaurants, live music and Oxford St - home of many gay friendly venues. Our area is also one of the oldest suburbs in Sydney and one with a colourful history - home to Sydney's underworld throughout the early 1900's. You can download a free tour app to learn about riots, criminals and mob bosses that ruled the area for more than 40 years. The CBD also offers lots to see and do - Hyde Park contains the war monument and is bord
notes: The apartment is accessible by en elevator so no stairs. There is 2hr street parking in the area, but it is difficult to leave a car for long periods. Check in time is normally 3pm and check out time is 10am. I often have back to back bookings and I outsource the cleaning so its important to allow the cleaners enough time to turnover the property. Many thanks
transit: Walking is the easiest and quickest way to get into the city, and you can travel on foot to most of Sydney's great attractions from the apartment. However if you want to go further it's a 2 minute walk to Museum Station on the City Circle train route which connects most of the suburban lines.  There is also a bus stop right outside with goes to Bondi Beach. Its also a short train ride to Circular Quay where you can any of the ferries on Sydney Harbour. To/From the airport. Taxi should cost between 35 and 40 and take around 25 mins depending on traffic. Alternatively you can catch the train which is about 15 one way - it takes you right into the city. Get off at Museum Station and walk 2 minutes up Liverpool St - super easy!

neighborhood_overview: Pyrmont has the convenience of being minutes from the CBD, Chinatown, Darling Harbour and the Rocks, but is leafy and has a creative, village like feel. There's a huge selection of cafes, bars, restaurants, boutiques and supermarkets right on your doorstep. The Sydney Fish Market and Chinese gardens are moments away and both are well worth a visit. The Star Casino is a few minutes walk away, as well as many of Sydney's main attractions including the Aquarium, Madam Tussauds, the Powerhouse Museum and the Maritime Museum. Chinatown is only a short walk or a short trip on the light rail tram, and the Ian Thorpe Aquatic and Fitness Centre is on the next corner.
notes: There's no real need for a car, we are super centrally located! The distances and comfortable walking times to major attractions, from the apartment follow - SHOPPING - Harbourside Shopping Centre 100m, 2 minutes Sydney Fish Markets 750 m 10 mins Queen Victoria Building 1.5 kms, 19 mins  Pitt St Mall, Sydney 1.6kms, 21 mins NIGHTLIFE - The Star 700m, 9 mins King Street Wharf 1.6 kms, 20 mins RESTAURANTS- Jones Bay Wharf 1 km, 12 mins Circular Quay 2.6kms, 32 mins Barangaroo 1.7kms, 21 mins ATTRACTIONS - Chinatown 1.1kms, 15 minutes Hyde Park, 1.8 kms, 24 mins The Domain 2.2kms, 29 mins The Rocks 2.4 kms, 30 mins Sydney Opera House 3.1 kms, 40 mins STATIONS - Sydney Convention Centre Light Rail, located opposite the apartment Central Station 1.7 kms, 21 mins Wynyard 1.8kms, 22 mins CAR RENTAL - Europcar is the closest car rental firm and they are located in the building next door, in Harris Street Pyrmont TRAVEL FROM THE AIRPORT - Either Uber or Taxis are great options or alternatively
transit: Buses leave from Harris Street in to the city constantly but it's far easier quicker to walk to the city (2 minutes across the bridge). There is a light rail (tram) across the street at Darling Harbour and at The Star Casino that takes you in to China Town and the CBD.  The area is very safe, well lit and walkable. The best thing is the apartment is in the centre of everything! To Sydney CBD: 10 minute walk To Sydney Harbour: You are on it! To China Town: 10 minute walk To Sydney Fish Market: 5 minute walk To Bondi Beach: 30 minutes by bus To Coogee Beach: 30 minutes by bus Secure Parking is the company that offers undercover parking in the building virtually next door and it's cheaper to book ahead online, via their website. The parking station is located at 320 Harris Street Pyrmont, however you access it via Camden Lane Pyrmont.

host_about:
I've been a big fan of Airbnb since discovering it on a trip to South America in 2013. Since then I have stayed in some amazing homes in places like Buenos Aires, Vienna, Melbourne and Kuala Lumpur.

I'm passionate about art, architecture, design, travel, history, food, wine and people! Career wise, I started out as a hostess in a restaurant, and now work in the corporate sector.

I'm really excited to now be an Airbnb host (and guest when I travel!) I look forward to meeting many more fabulous people along the way!

neighborhood_overview: The ultimate location for work or visiting Sydney, our apartment is located on the edge of Hyde Park in the heart of Sydney's CBD. Walk out the front door and you are just a few steps to the sprawling lawns of beautiful Hyde Park, great for a morning jog or escape the city and warm up in the sun.  Everything is convenient and you won't be needing any taxis! It's an easy stroll down to the Harbour Bridge & Opera House. It's also a short walk to Darling Harbour, Chinatown, and into the restaurant/cafe precinct in Surry Hills where all of the best restaurants are located.  If you're visiting for work, who cares about traffic or the bothers of public transport when it's just an easy walk to & from the office!  We love this location - all of Sydney's best is on our doorstep and it allows each day to be enjoyed fully. The public transport network in Sydney is not great and taxis are expensive, so in this location we can live stress-free and take in all of the wonderful things that life in Sy

host_about:
Nous avons emménagé à Nadaillac de Rouge en Août 2016.
Nous avons adoré la région puisqu'elle est au milieu de la plupart des sites du Lot, de la Corrèze et de la Dordogne.

Nous avons vécu en Australie  (Sydney) et c'est là bas que nous nous sommes rencontrés il y a maintenant 6 ans. 
Javier est equatorien/australien 
(Il a aussi vécu a Cuba et aux USA),
Je suis français/australien
(J'ai aussi vécu en Inde)
Nous parlons français, espagnol, portugais et anglais.

On a été hôtes l'année dernière à Sydney et on a vraiment adoré !
Rencontrer des gens du monde entier était excellent et nous sommes même devenus amis avec certains.
Partager des moments ensemble, faire en sorte que leur voyage soit le plus agréable possible et surtout qu'ils se sentent à la maison était  très important pour nous. 


We moved to Nadaillac de Rouge in August 2016. We loved this area sitting in the middle of the touristic sites of the Dordogne, Corrèze and Lot regions.

We used to live in Australia  (Sydney) and met there 6 years ago. 
Javier is Ecuadorian/Australian 
(he also lived in the Usa, Cuba)
I am French/Australian 
(i also lived in India)
We speak French, Spanish, Portuguese and English.

We experienced hosting in Sydney last year and loved it! We enjoyed meeting people from all around the world and some even became good friends.
Sharing some time with them, helping to make their trip as easy as possible and making sure they feel at home was very important for us.

neighborhood_overview: Impressive and extremely convenient surroundings. We're situated on Clarence St in Sydney's CBD, in-between Darling Harbour and Wynyard Station. There’s really nowhere in the world quite like Darling Harbour. From first light to starry nights, there’s always something going on here. Coffee machines froth, water laps, children play, friends chat, steaks sear, glasses clink, bass thumps and fireworks crackle. Infectious sounds travel on harbour breezes as text messages and online updates share snapshots of good times. There are tons of things to do in the city itself which are mostly a quick stroll away. I've included most of my favorite places and more in my extensive "Local Recommendations Guidebook" on this listings page, so please feel free to check em' out for awesome things to do and eat in the CBD area.

notes: As we do not offer whole of house our guests tend to be busy , short term ones who are out most of the time. transit: Guests can walk to a beautiful harbour side beach . If travelling to the city we recommend bus which involves a five minute walk to bus stop and ten minute bus ride.

Obviously we see guests at breakfast and when guests know where everything is we are happy for you to help yourself.
house_rules: We do not have strict check in / out times preferring to say AM / PM with common sense pervading and are happy for guests to park their luggage before check in or after check out. No pets allowed as we already have a lovely  dog  called Reacher As we are sharing our home we expect guests to be polite and respectful but so far, all have been! The upstairs 2 bedrooms and upstairs bathroom are for guests exclusive use. Whilst we say washing machine and dryer available that is within reason - i.e. a weeks washing and drying for four we would see as too much - a bit of washing to get by o.k. - common sense rules .

My wife Helen and myself have lived in this house since 1978 and have raised three children here. They have gone of course leaving a fabulous private upstairs space available for guests. With two bedrooms and bathroom for exclusive use of guests our space is suitable for overnight stay but not ideal for an extended stay when the the common areas of the house would be used extensively .-

host_about:
I'm originally from the UK but moved to Australia with my husband four and half years ago to start our next life adventure together.

We love to travel and have both spent time living and working overseas. Currently we're based between Sydney and Woy Woy on the Central Coast. 

Justin and I are quite a chilled out couple. We're both very clean and tidy and respectful of other peoples privacy. 

We keep ourselves busy with our two companies - a web agency and a digital advertising agency, so when we're at home we're usually perched in front of a laptop. We've also welcomed a little fur baby into our lives - our puppy Sheba who keeps us occupied in all the other spare minutes of the day.

We love meeting new people so let us know if you'd like to catch up for a coffee or glass of wine and share some stories.

name: Charming East Balmain apartment
space: This delightful first floor apartment is just what you need for a week or a weekend in Sydney. Only a few minutes walk from both the Darling Street ferry wharf and East Balmain's waterfront parks. . Buses into the city stop at the end of the street and there is an alternative wharf - Balmain wharf - at Mort Bay about 15-20 minutes walk up the street. It can also be reached by a short bus ride and a 5-10 minutes walk.) There are cafes, restaurants, shopping and a great pub just around the corner so you probably won't even use the well equipped kitchen.  Or you can head over to many of the numerous parks that line the harbour and have a picnic. The apartment has a double brass bed in the bedroom and a double sofa bed in the living room  . All linen and towels are provided. There is also parking available. You may want to spend a moment sitting on the balcony admiring  the Harbour Bridge views but my guess is you will want to jump straight onto one of the passing ferries and explore Sydne

house_rules: Our apartment is on the first floor of one of the earliest buildings in Balmain. It has lovely high ceilings and a sense of bygone days despite the modern kitchen and more contemporary furnishings. There is a coin operated laundry with a washer and dryer at the back of the building which we share with the others. We also have a garage which may be available during your stay with us. This is not a high tech ultra-modern pad. It is quaint and quiet and will suit those of you looking for an opportunity to experience the culture of East Balmain. Our apartment is unique and in a very special building and as such we cannot permit any smoking either inside or outside on our balcony.
host_about: We are inveterate travellers who love meeting other travellers and we delight in introducing Balmain (and Sydney) to guests from interstate and overseas.

neighborhood_overview: Due to all the surrounding neighbourhood businesses and the adjacent shopping centre, Marion Street is well serviced and always full of life and activity.  It is a real and authentic suburb of Sydney that is not a tourist make-over. Norton Street is also a short 10 minute walk away. It is the main shopping strip of Leichhardt, with a cool cinema and other large shopping centres, as well as many quirky shops and good restaurants. In Leichhardt there are many parks, sports areas, an excellent aquatic centre and more. Iron Cove Bay is just down the hill and that has a great 8 km. walk-run-cycle circuit commonly called the Bay Run.
notes: GENERALLY  A mix of Ghetto and Little Italy......our home is simple, grungy, crude, casual, artistic, unusual.....definitely far from perfect.  It has a crazy hip-hop style mixed with old-school rustic ambiance.....the place has mood and attitude ;-) It's a work in progress with parts incomplete, raw, rudimentary and skeletal. Nevertheless, in our opinion it feels organic, natural and relaxed. It's a no fuss place. Nothing too delicate and fine. It's easy to just 'hang-out and chill' here.  It has real people and a sense of history too. Travellers come and go, yet here too is a journey..... Despite the 'chic & shock' of our urban graffiti decor, it's still our home and we welcome you to make it yours too. THE ENTRANCE It's an unusual looking entrance; somewhat  'dark n weird' , so try not to run away. Take courage and it will get better as you rise....;-) I personally prefer a dark candle-lit gothic ambiance. I find it easy, soft and subtle on the eye. It also adds a lot of depth and i
transit: GENERALLY: Marion St is very accessible and transport is readily available. BUSES: Bus-Stops are 30 meters away or 1 minute walk. LIGHT RAIL (Tram): The station is a 5 minutes walk away. TRAINS: Petersham Metro Train Station is just 10 minutes away by bus. There are 2 train stations within 1.8 km.  CAR: parking is usually available on adjacent streets. They are unmetered. BIKE: A house bike is available for guests. Here is some general travel information for you :)  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ CONVENIENT TRAVEL  TO & FROM THE AIRPAD ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ * Please check Reviews.  There are some general comments on the issue, such as  'conveniently located' & 'getting around is easy'. Opal Transport Cards allows cheap and integrated use of buses, trains, light rail (trams) and ferries. For your general info, the bus stop is 20metres or 1 minute away on Marion Street.  "Too easy".,,,;-) The AirPad is located on a main bus route to the city; travelling along Parramatta Road, b
access: CHECK-IN TIME Guests can access the AirPad upon specified check-in time is usually 3pm. However, upon request I may be flexible with early or very late check-in times. I usually; but not always, block-out the day before each reservation in order to allow guests the possibility of an early check-in.  I try to assist all my guests; but especially international travellers, who arrive at airports at unpredictable hours. I don't like my guests to be troubled by long waits for check-in; especially with lots of luggage to cart around. INSTANT BOOKING: Should this setting be 'on' at the time:- PLEASE MAKE SURE  YOU ARRANGE FOR  ANY ALTERNATIVE CHECK-IN TIME WITH ME 'BEFORE' YOU INSTANT BOOK. ARRIVAL NOTICE: Please notify your Expected Arrival Time in advance of your Arrival Date. Prior to Check-in, please also contact me at least 1 hour prior to your Actual Arrival Time in order to assure access into the apartment and also a proper reception. This also help me in case you are experiencing flig
interaction: We aim to keep things natural and easy. We are happy to appropriately interact or allow plenty of independence. We are also pleased to assist with any problems that you may have and provide guidance, information or directions.
house_rules: GENERAL:- I do not usually judge, choose or select. Guests are chosen on a first come, first serve basis. This has not been a problem for me because 98% of guest are 'normal'; no matter what origins or background. My guests are usually fantastic people and I do not need to 'curb or cull' behaviour with my preconceived ideas of courtesy, respect and good manners.  Therefore the following information is written for the 2% of irregular and 'unruly' types, that need basic house rules to be 'spelt out'; albeit with all due respect. Please don't assume that 'easy access' into my home means that 'I don't care', or I don't have expectation, or this is a license to stretch the limits of courtesy and respect, or that I will not act to correct misbehaviour. Take special note that this is a communal 'guest home' and not a private commercial 'boarding house'. The care-factor is certainly far greater that the basic financial dealing at hand. I can easily let go of the business because the Airbnb inc
host_about:
I was born in Spain, but have grown up here in Sydney since I was 5 years old. I can speak fluent Spanish and have travelled back there many times, as well as many other places. It’s now been some time since I have made a journey overseas. Hopefully this will happen in the near future. But in the meantime, I look forward to meeting wonderful travelers adventuring here in Australia via Airbnb. This global community makes me feel that I too belong to a world of friendly and likeminded people seeking wonderful and unique experiences. No matter where people come from, it’s amazing to see how much we have in common. I just love the way that unknown people and places can become familiar and meaningful.
I have lived in Leichhardt for the last 20 years. Our shop-top apartment is our home. I do love it here in Sydney and feel that this is my place, home, culture. I am happy to host with conviction because it comes naturally. 
I am also a busy working person and am usually out and about. When I am at home, I am easy going and approach things in an easy and non-intrusive way. However, I can also be communicative and engaging. I am generous in nature and happy to share. I will most certainly aim to facilitate and make your stay as pleasant as I can. I am very willing to point you in the right direction.
My interests are design, arts and especially architecture. I am also keen on building construction projects, environmental issues and community matters.

interaction: We travel very often so you will not be able to reach me on my phone. Messaging is always the best way to get in touch with me.  We may or may not be present at the time of your stay.  Our flatmate is home every day but he is not your "host".  You do need to be self sufficient and able to find your own way around.  You wouldn't believe the dozens of questions I get from potential guests. Seriously guys... Web search it first. If you still need help, then please message me.  :)
house_rules: - Please clean up after yourself immediately and do not use or consume other peoples products or food. Supply your own laundry liquid and do not use the dryer.  - Be respectful of others sleeping when arriving or leaving. Do not invite friends to the property without consent.  - If you break something or stain the carpet or bedding you must cover the cost to repair or replace it as it was or better.  - Remove your own rubbish and recycling from the property. - Please take shoes off at the door and use the shoe rack to store them.  - Keep personal belongings tidy and out of the way. - Clean up after yourself in the bathroom and kitchen.  - Use only what you pay for, or ask first and the replace what you use.  - I don't mind a glass or two of wine but please keep the party for the City. I live in a building with young families and retired people. Plus I work from home. - There is also a 15 penalty for lost house keys.  - Any costs incurred from damage  in or to the property will be clai
host_about:
In our home we recycle, compost, grown our own vegetables, conserve water and prefer to cook healthy whole food instead of packaged things. 

At the moment myself and my husband are living in New Zealand as his mother is terminal and we do not want to be away from her. While we are away we have opened our home to travellers from all over the world who want a budget and safe place to stay.

It's not hotel fancy but we love our little green home and hope you enjoy your stay.

We also advocate for womens rights and believe we can live in a stronger and more peaceful world. 

One day we would like to travel the world with my our children to expose them to how beautiful and powerful our planet is. I believe we are all one human race and our differences make us beautiful.

neighborhood_overview: • Located in probably Australia's most famous and iconic suburb:(URL HIDDEN)Bondi Beach • The sand on Bondi Beach is literally a 2-minute skip from your doorstep! • Only a minute's walk to buses that connect to central transport hubs    that will take you anywhere around Sydney • You're just a brief ride away from famous Sydney suburbs and neighbourhoods like Watsons Bay, Double Bay, Kings Cross, and walking distance from the famous Eastern Suburbs beaches of Tamarama, Bronte, Clovelly, Gordons Bay and Coogee • You are surrounded by countless bars, restaurants, coffee shops, doctors, pharmacies, fashion and convenience stores • Bondi Junction – one of Sydney's major retail, shopping and transportation hubs – is located in the next suburb and is easy to get to
notes: Have a pet? Should be no problem… but please ask us first. To ensure that all of our guests have the perfect summer vacation, we've set a minimum of a five [5]  day booking for the summer months.  Check-in is at 3pm, and check-out is by 11am. Arriving slightly earlier, or want that extra hour to sleep? Should be fine, but again, please check with us first.
transit: TRAINS: Trains can be caught from Bondi Junction  BUSES: 2 minute walk to buses that take you to Bondi Junction, from where you can get countless buses (or trains) to hundreds of spots all around Sydney. We are also 2 minutes' walk to buses that will take you to the famous ‘Gap' lookout point in Watsons Bay, as well as multiple vantage point parks for capturing that perfect panoramic scene of Sydney Harbour, the famous Opera House, and of course, the Sydney Harbour Bridge ! TAXIS: Readily available taxis constantly driving past apartment building and surrounding streets. Uber and other internet based taxi-ride services are also available in Sydney. FERRY: For the perfect Sydney holiday experience, get around via our stunning harbour! The ferry can be caught from Rose Bay ferry stop – just a five minute drive or half hour walk from the apartment. PARKING: A single complimentary parking spot is provided right at your front door (a rare treat in this exclusive and popular neighborhood!)
access: ACCESS TO EVERYTHING – FEEL LIKE IT'S YOUR HOME: • Complete and uninterrupted access to all areas of the entire apartment • Direct access from your personal living room to adjoining garden retreat • TV, WiFi, Foxtel cable TV, home furnishings and full appliance-stocked kitchen and internal laundry  • FREE reserved car parking space at your front door - rare for Bondi !
interaction: I like to ensure your vacation starts off on the right foot.  I will personally greet you upon arrival, or if more convenient you can utilise the key-safe system at the front door and let yourself in. I'm always happy to also give you a quick run-down on the local area. I'm happy to provide recommendations and advice or anything else that might pop up during your stay. Throughout your stay, I'm only ever a phone call away, or feel free to drop me an email if that's easier for you.
house_rules: As you can see, this is a family home in a residential area. If coming to Sydney to party, you've picked a great city to do so. Unfortunately just not at our place. Though we are sure it won't come to it, serious complaints of unruly behavior will unfortunately result in you being asked to leave. Not good for you. Not good for us. And being a family home, we also have a no smoking policy (although you are welcome to smoke either out front or back). To make sure we keep the place and all amenities in tip-top condition, we've set a maximum occupancy of 6 (+ 1 baby). Please respect this.
host_about:
Hi there. I’m Esther. I’m proud to say I’ve been a Sydney local for over 60 years, and I couldn’t imagine living anywhere else.

I love it here because there’s something magical in the Sydney Air. It’s the perfect combination of a living amidst a beautiful harbor city, with laid-back people and a never-ending list of fun and exciting things going on all months of the year.

Now that I’m retired, I like to fill up my days with the things I enjoy the most – going for walks (I live in a great city to do this!), playing bridge and trying to improve my photography skills (again… a great city for this too!)
 
I enjoy travelling the world and experiencing different cultures . My favourite countries are Italy, France and Argentina. Through these travels, I’ve been fortunate to learn what a good Airbnb experience (and host) looks like: A great home, with a friendly host, in a great neighbourhood, and the ability to do the things you love! I try ensure that each and every guest I host walks away with all of that and hopefully more.

Like most Aussies, I like to keep a laid-back attitude to life. As they say - don’t worry about the world ending today… it’s already tomorrow in Australia.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is a peaceful oasis in the heart of one of Sydney's most dynamic, buzzing areas, just minutes from the cafes, restaurants, bars and shops of Oxford Street, Victoria Street, Potts Point and Kings Cross.  Darlinghurst and Surry Hills offer an eclectic mix of art, design, fashion and food. Vintage boutiques and hidden haunts combine with a genuine neighbourhood vibe and some of Sydney’s best cafes (Bills, Room 10, Yellow) restaurants (Phamish, Billy Kwong, Red Lantern, Marque, Apollo), small bars (Love Tilly Divine, Hinky Dinks), and theatres.  Australia’s best ice cream parlour – Gelato Messina – on the doorstep.
transit: There are plenty of buses just minutes away on William Street, Liverpool Street and Oxford Street which offer public transport to the city, Circular Quay (Sydney Opera House), Bondi Beach and  other beaches. A comfortable 15 minutes’ walk takes you to the heart of the city’s main shopping area or the Botanic Gardens and harbour, Art Gallery of New South Wales, Hyde Park, the Australian Museum or St Mary’s Cathedral. Plus many car share vehicles are located directly in the street. A 30 minute walk will get you to Belvoir St Theatre, Central Station, Sydney Football Stadium and Cricket ground, Centennial Park and Entertainment Quarter.

You will be just a Lift ride and a short walk away from China Town, Town Hall Station, Bars, Clubs, World Square, George St, Cinemas, Shopping Centres, Museums, Art Galleries and of course all of the amazing food option Sydney CBD has to offer.  For the traveller who wants to be close to it all this is the place!

I've made a comprehensive guide to the city of things that are close, restaurants I like and things that you can do. But of course if you would like some specific recommendations let me know what you are into and looking for and i'll try my best!
host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

It has a mixture of business and residential activity and it's neighbours are Mosman and Neutral Bay.  This area is called the Lower North Shore and from the apartment the bus will get you into the city within 15mins and is only approximately 25 mins by car from the airport.
