neighborhood_overview: Pyrmont has the convenience of being minutes from the CBD, Chinatown, Darling Harbour and the Rocks, but is leafy and has a creative, village like feel. There's a huge selection of cafes, bars, restaurants, boutiques and supermarkets right on your doorstep. The Sydney Fish Market and Chinese gardens are moments away and both are well worth a visit. The Star Casino is a few minutes walk away, as well as many of Sydney's main attractions including the Aquarium, Madam Tussauds, the Powerhouse Museum and the Maritime Museum. Chinatown is only a short walk or a short trip on the light rail tram, and the Ian Thorpe Aquatic and Fitness Centre is on the next corner.
notes: There's no real need for a car, we are super centrally located! The distances and comfortable walking times to major attractions, from the apartment follow - SHOPPING - Harbourside Shopping Centre 100m, 2 minutes Sydney Fish Markets 750 m 10 mins Queen Victoria Building 1.5 kms, 19 mins  Pitt St Mall, Sydney 1.6kms, 21 mins NIGHTLIFE - The Star 700m, 9 mins King Street Wharf 1.6 kms, 20 mins RESTAURANTS- Jones Bay Wharf 1 km, 12 mins Circular Quay 2.6kms, 32 mins Barangaroo 1.7kms, 21 mins ATTRACTIONS - Chinatown 1.1kms, 15 minutes Hyde Park, 1.8 kms, 24 mins The Domain 2.2kms, 29 mins The Rocks 2.4 kms, 30 mins Sydney Opera House 3.1 kms, 40 mins STATIONS - Sydney Convention Centre Light Rail, located opposite the apartment Central Station 1.7 kms, 21 mins Wynyard 1.8kms, 22 mins CAR RENTAL - Europcar is the closest car rental firm and they are located in the building next door, in Harris Street Pyrmont TRAVEL FROM THE AIRPORT - Either Uber or Taxis are great options or alternatively
transit: Buses leave from Harris Street in to the city constantly but it's far easier quicker to walk to the city (2 minutes across the bridge). There is a light rail (tram) across the street at Darling Harbour and at The Star Casino that takes you in to China Town and the CBD.  The area is very safe, well lit and walkable. The best thing is the apartment is in the centre of everything! To Sydney CBD: 10 minute walk To Sydney Harbour: You are on it! To China Town: 10 minute walk To Sydney Fish Market: 5 minute walk To Bondi Beach: 30 minutes by bus To Coogee Beach: 30 minutes by bus Secure Parking is the company that offers undercover parking in the building virtually next door and it's cheaper to book ahead online, via their website. The parking station is located at 320 Harris Street Pyrmont, however you access it via Camden Lane Pyrmont.
access: All of it! A huge two storey, two bedroom, two bathroom warehouse loft. Please note - that there is a hotel that shares the same building however we are not at all associated. As a result we ask guests not to make requests of the front desk staff or Conceirge. If you accidentally set off the fire alarm however please inform the Conceirge immediately on (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN). We also unfortunately cannot offer any luggage storage facilities.  If you require any assistance during your stay please contact us, we're happy to assist!

I'm really excited to now be an Airbnb host (and guest when I travel!) I look forward to meeting many more fabulous people along the way!

description: Very spacious apartment overlooking Rose Bay! My partner and I live in one bedroom and we have a spare room to anyone who would like to experience Rose Bay! Art deco style place.  15 mins from the CBD, you can catch the Ferry to Circular Quay or a direct bus outside the door.  Own private room, ample space. Separate dining and lounge room, kitchen and bathroom. Washing machine. There are two Japanese restaurants and an Indian restaurant within 3 mins walking distance from the place. A 5 min stroll away is the famous Plumer road chicken shop! 3 cafes, a bottle-shop, pharmacy, newsagent and gourmet deli. Rosebay main street is a 5 min drive or 15 min walk away. The eastern suburbs are like a magical escape from the city, while still living in central Sydney. Watson's bay is just a ferry ride away and Bondi beach is a 30 min walk away!  Included: Washing Machine Kettle
neighborhood_overview: An energetic part of Sydney, with a mix of young people, families and walking enthusiasts - with the water's edge just across the road, a walk around the bay is a popular idea.
transit: There is a bus stop almost virtually out the front of the building that takes you into town. There is also (most preferred mode of transport) the ferry which can take you either in to town or over to iconic Watson's Bay (and various stops in-between)
house_rules: This is a friendly house, however it is not for parties! :)

neighborhood_overview: Potts Point is one of Sydneys best neighborhood. Friendly, close, hip and safe. Home to some of the trendiest cafes, restaurants and boutiques, you’ll feel as though you've stumbled upon a little patch of Paris (yes, some clichés exist for a reason: the "Potts Point is like Paris" line is one such cliché... ) Tree-lined streets, gorgeous old art deco buildings, stunning views and the eclectic mix of amazing locals. Potts Point is close to everything, walking distance to the city and all landmarks. On one hand you have the Botanic gardens, Opera house and ABC pool, on the other hand cafes, train station, restaurants and shopping. Three big parks around the corner just waiting for you to grab a blanket and hang out people watching. Potts Point is as great and appreciated amongst families as a group of girlfriends looking for a good time or couples wanting amazing food to explore hand in hand.
notes: We provide you with beach towels, umbrellas, picnic blanket, cooler, boogie board etc. If you have special requests we are happy to look in to that.
transit: The apartment is extraordinary well located.  If you are arriving from the airport you take the Airport train to Town Hall, make an easy change to a local train, which runs all the time with high frequency, and get of at the stop called "Kings Cross" and walk around 400 meters. This will in total take you about 20 min. By cab  from the airport in-between 15-35 min depending on traffic. The city center and all the famous landmarks are in walking distance. If you prefer to take the train that will take you 5 min from Kings Cross. Overall the communications from this area are the best in Sydney.
access: You will have the whole apartment to yourself and we love for you to use it as if it was your home
interaction: We love Sydney and also love hosting. How much interaction is up to you! We will be at hand any time all hours during your stay if you need us. You can reach us by phone, text or email, what you prefer. We also have a backup person standby incase you can't reach us. We are more then happy to give you suggestions on everything from breakfast places to creating a full day walk around tour.  We welcome you to experience the amazing life of a Sydneysider!
house_rules: No smoking in the apartment  No loud music after 10pm  No party or bigger gatherings  No other people staying other than booked named guests Please know that during your stay you are responsible for the keys. We love to host and be at your service but we are not a 24/7 open hotel, if you lose the key or lock yourself out we will of course do everything in our power to get you back in asap but if we are traveling and can't assist you or, due to other circumstances, you need to use a locksmith this cost is on you. We hope you feel at home and treat our apartment and neighbours with respect.
host_about: I'm a Swedish viking enjoying life under the blue sky in the city of my dreams. I kickbox, hike, bike and run every chance I get. I'm a bit of a health nut, slightly addicted to greens. I consider a couple of cucumbers as perfect long haul flight-snack and if I got stuck on a deserted island with only avocado + coconuts I would be a happy girl. But don’t worry I also love to bake Swedish delicacies such as Cinnamon rolls and ”Semla” and I make a mean Espresso Martini. Passionately love Sydney and try to visit a new restaurant, cafe, place every week to stay up to date. Happy to give you all our recommendation on everything from best bar, perfect pre-work run, must do´s etc. Beside from Sydney other favorite destinations are: Copenhagen, Palm Springs, anywhere in the Greek islands, Hawaii or why not a snowy ski slope finished with hot coca! Hope to meet you!

transit: Buses and trains are all at your disposable. The Opal card is the way to go when catching public transport and is available from any newsagency. There is one conveniently located on Darlinghurst Road on the way to the train station and bus stop on Bayswater Road. You can download the Tripview app to organise your trips and travel time. Although if the weather is right then walking  is the perfect way to see Sydney. Sydney City Shuttle  (phone number hidden)  Does drop offs between Sydney Airport and The Kirketon Hotel (only 2 doors away).  So make sure you mention the name of this hotel when you are booking. Taxis are easy to catch from the front of the building. UBER is super popular in Sydney, so download the app for discounted private taxi rates. Download the Trip View app to get all the latest updates and information on buses, trains and ferries.
access: Rooftop terrace, pool, laundry room and BBQ and Free on street parking - a one day temporary permit needs to be issues from myself for each day. Be welcomed by me downstairs ready to help you with your luggage. If your early before the allocated check in time, i have a spare apartment where you can freshen up with a shower, have a lie down or leave your bags to go exploring! There are a few refreshments in the fridge and plenty of goodies in the cupboard above for your enjoyment after that long flight. All towels and bed linen changed after 1 week.
interaction: Interaction is my favourite thing. If i'm not away i'm here all of the time, and here to answer any questions or give you the best recommendations possible.
house_rules: This is my home and i would expect others to treat it as they would their own. If you are a smoker then i would appreciate it if you would use the rooftop terrace, the view is way better! Rooftop hours are from 6am to 10pm. Limit of 5 people to the rooftop. Strict no party policy!
host_about:
Love theatre, music, food and wine. Nothing better than catching up with old and new friends.
Keep fit by dog walking and gym workouts.

Am a self-employed masssage therapist, so feel free to hit up for a relaxing massage to ease all your aches and pains after those long plane flights.

Have been an Airbnb host since September 2014.... and is there is absolutely nothing i enjoy more than welcoming people to my city and meeting new people.
Im super friendly and will bend over backwards to help you have the best stay possible.

Have travelled to Scotland, UK, Indonesia, Thailand, Dubai and Germany.

Be kind to everyone - Jim Henson

LGBTI Friendly :-))

neighborhood_overview: Absolutely everything at your footstep from Chinatown, to Darling Harbour to the bustling CBD and main transport railway/bus stations. World Square shopping center is just down the street in 2 mins walk and 5 mins walk to Pitt Street shopping including Westfield mall and high end fashion. It is about 10 min walk towards the Opera House/Harbour bridge. Also 10 minutes walk to Pitt St mall for all your shopping needs. You'll have heaps of food options to choose from. It depends on your tastes but I can recommend my personal favourites : Chat Thai 20 Campbell St. Haymarket - best Thai food Haymarket Hotel - Cheapest but excellent australian steak and chips deal for only 12 Din Tai Fung World Square - fantastic dumplings. Also try Uncle Mings on York Street. Macchiato Wood Fire Pizza corner liverpool and Pitt Street for Italian food. Also try  Vapiano on York Street. It is just a street away from Hyde Park where you can catch many buses to the Eastern suburbs including Bondi Beach and Coo

For the record I haven't made any claims to date.
transit: The apartment is a short walk between 2 major train stations in the city. You can find Town Hall station or Museum station just a short 2-5 min walk depending on which direction. The transport system is simple now you just buy a card called "Opal" that you can use to catch trains, ferries and buses.

Otherwise there's plenty of public transport close by Light Rail to City Central and Bus route 443 to the CBD, shopping district and Circular Quay

(The main bedroom has a king size bed and ensuite and the second has a queen size bed and own bathroom) This contemporary apartment is a five minute  walk to Darling Harbour and two minutes to The Star Casino and the Fish Markets and an easy 15 minute walk or 10 minute bus ride to Sydney's CBD. It's a safe area to walk around in a very friendly part of Sydney with loc
neighborhood_overview: The apartment complex is fairly small (seven storeys), very well maintained and right on the water. The area is known as Jacksons Landing and most apartment blocks were built ten or less years ago so it has a modern feel. However, there are examples of some of the history. It has a safe, friendly feel to it - quite a few restaurants, great pubs with good food and regular public transport (bus and light rail) Guests should enjoy a walk around the waterfront to the Fishmarkets to Glebe and/or the other way to Jones Bay Wharf and Darling Harbour. Sydney's CBD is a pleasant 15 minute walk.
notes: Vivid Sydney is on in May and June with some events within walking distance.  A couple of guests have had parties but unfortunately this is not allowed as this is purely for accommodation and for guests (maximum four) to enjoy the apartment. Bookings must be of minimum 2 days. A minimum of five days is required over Christmas and New Year.
transit: The regular bus 443 (a two minute walk from the apartment) goes to the city centre and main ferry terminal at Circular Quay about every ten minutes  It's a ten minute trip to the CBD (which can be walked in less than 20 minutes). There's also light rail (2 minutes walk to the stop) which goes via Darling Harbour to Central Station and Chinatown. Brochures and information will be at my apartment for guests' use.
access: The guests and I communicate by email or text before arrival day. Guests need to ring on arrival so I can come down to let them in or give them the code to enter. Some cupboards are closed to guests but otherwise this gorgeous apartment is yours to enjoy for the duration of your stay.
interaction: Once the booking is confirmed I comminicate with guests before arrival via email or phone and on arrival I meet them to briefly explain what's what, go through any questions they may have and to hand over keys. Otherwise, I'm available on my mobile for contact via phone or text.
house_rules: Information for the use of electrical equipment and cable TV, dishwasher etc are printed out for guest reference. There is only one neighbour on the same floor but we use the same lift and garbage shute room so we respect each other's privacy.  No pets are allowed. No smoking permitted inside. No parties please and maximum four guests.
host_about: For the last twelve years I have enjoyed apartment living on the waterfront and close to the city's amenities. Having moved from a 'leafy northern suburb' I appreciate walking along the waterfront, having the CBD easily accessible either by excellent public transport or a 15 minute walk through Darling Harbour and being close to many and varied restaurants, pubs and cafes.

host_about: Hi! We are Luke and Rebecca and we have been hosting on AirBnB since December 2016 and we love it so far! For us as hosts it is really important to us that we treat guests exactly as we would want to be treated and that means fast communication and providing great value accomodation in the heart of Darling Harbour. We are both fairly well traveled - Rebecca is originally from Ireland and has lived in Germany, the US and Australia (since October 2012) and Luke is from New York and have lived in several states in the US, the Czech Republic and Australia (twice - most recently since August 2012). We have lived in Pyrmont for about two years and love it's small village vibe and its proximity to the city. When travelling we love adventure! You are unlikely to find us lounging by the pool!

name: Apartment with Sydney Harbour views
summary: A clean & bright unit, with beautiful views stretching from the famous Bondi beach to Sydney harbour and the iconic Sydney skyline. A main bedroom with attached sunroom. There is also a small study converted into a single bedroom, should you require a 3rd guest. A combined lounge/dining area opens onto large balcony. Tv/Dvd/Netflix. space: Our apartment complex has a pool, spa and small gym which guests may use. There is visitor parking available.  The apartment faces north and gets full sun all day, and many guests enjoy breakfast or a long lunch on the balcony looking across to the Opera House and Harbour Bridge in the distance.  Inside the apartment there is some wardrobe space to hang your clothes, and a fully stocked kitchen where you are welcome to use anything to cook.  Towels and linens all included, and extras available if you need during your stay.  We provide you with fresh juice, tea, milk, bread, butter, cereal and a few snacks for your arrival. We know the feeling of stepping off a 24 hour flight and needing a cup of tea and toast immediately! But you are welcome to help yourself to any other items in the kitchen.  Any questions give us a yell!

neighborhood_overview: Bondi Junction is the perfect balance between the city and the sea. We have one of the largest Westfield Shopping centres in Sydney, home to major international brands and fantastic eateries. There is also a major cinema and multiple grocery stores for all your needs. Just down the road from Bondi Junction towards the city is the very fashionable Woollahra and Paddington neighbourhoods. These are full to the brim with high end boutiques, delightful cafes, bookstores and an arthouse theatre. Down the hill the other way is Bondi and the iconic Bondi Beach, with restaurants, cafes, markets, and plenty of nightlife. Centennial park is a short walk away, with bicycle riding paths, playing fields, walking tracks and wonderful picnic areas, a perfect way to spend a sunny afternoon. Our favorite places to eat include the Nelson Bay Tuck Shop (fresh healthy breakfasts / brunch), El Topo (mexican on top of Eastern Hotel), guzman and gomez (mexican takeaway chain), Arthurs Pizza and Bondi Pizza,
transit: Bondi Junction is a major transport hub. Bondi Junction train station is at the end of the T4 Eastern suburbs line. This takes you directly into the CBD to Town Hall and Central Stations, where you can access the entire Sydney train, bus and ferry network. On top of the train station is the Bondi Junction bus interchange. From here you can catch buses direct to Bondi beach, as well as other famous beaches around the eastern suburbs such as Bronte, Coogee and Maroubra.  Buses will also take you towards the city, stopping near the boutiques and cafes along Oxford Street in Paddington & Woollahra, and onto to Hyde Park and the CBD. We are also located a 20min walk from the iconic Sydney Cricket Ground and Sydney Football stadium, should your stay involve any sporting or concert events there.
access: Guests will have access to the entire apartment. There is a balcony accessible from the loungroom with great views towards Sydney harbour and back towards Bondi. There is a gym in the building for residents only, that guests can access. As well as a heated lap pool and spa next to the gym. Visitor parking is also available for guests.
interaction: At this stage I am opening the apartment while I'm away, so there will be little interaction sadly. On most occasions my adult children will facilitate your arrival and departure. On rare occasions they may need to access some stored items in the spare bedroom during your stay, however this will be confirmed and negotiated with you before arrival.
house_rules: We only ask that you treat this place as if it were your own home. We want you to be comfortable and feel free to make use of all the facilities available, but just ask that you leave the place clean and tidy upon your departure. No smoking at all inside the apartment please. Preferred non-smokers, but if the urge strikes, then please take yourself onto the balcony and close the sliding door. Thank you. Check out is 10am but we are happy to facilitate a late check out if there are no other guests booked, just give us a shout. Please also contact us to arrange your check in time.

name: Cosy Practical Base Camp for Sydney Explorers
summary: This is a functional, pleasant place with a few bonus features - balcony, car space, air conditioning, Foxtel and wifi.  It's about as small as 2 bedroom flats come, but we've been very happy here for more than 10yrs.  It's well located between the city and eastern beaches with 24hr bus transport.  A magnificent huge park is a few minutes walk away.   We usually lend the flat to friends when we go away but when there are no takers, Airbnb can help fund our holiday accommodation.
space: The thing to note is that the flat is small and not really suitable for more than 2 adults, 3 tops.    You could wedge in up to 3 kids in the little room, on the sofa bed and on a mattress on the floor...but it sure would be cramped.  It would be perfect for a couple who would use the little room as a dressing/luggage room.  It's our home, and we'll try to leave surfaces clutter free, but the wardrobe and cupboard space is very limited.   There's a separate laundry but there's no clothes dryer.  This is because there are good outdoor and undercover shared washing lines downstairs.

neighborhood_overview: Centennial Park the suburb consists of just a few streets, named after the actual park.  A real gift.  Explore it on the net before you come.  An enormous space so close to the city.  It has cycling and running tracks, ponds with ducks and black swans, a cafe, an outdoor cinema in summer....oh and the trees - paperbarks, eucalyptus, figs and ferns.   To have this on our doorstep AND so many urban offerings is really unique.   Adjacent suburbs within walking distance are Paddington (Saturday markets, cafes, trendy clothes, a dozen pubs and the Oxford St vibe), Woollahra, Randwick (Racecourse and University of NSW beyond), Moore Park (The Sydney Cricket Ground and Football Stadium, Fox Studios and the Entertainment Quarter - loads of cinemas and bars)  and Bondi Junction (mega-mall and train station).
notes: Here are some reasons why this might not suit you (yes really!); You're very tall and you've always had queen or king beds.  A double bed could be a problem. Heather's an informal kind of person who doesn't iron the pillowcases or fold the end of the toilet paper.   The place is smoke and pet free There's no gym or pool or other mod cons.  The kitchen is not stainless steel or caesar stone and does not have Smeg appliances, a dishwasher or a clothes dryer. The shower is over the bath and your knees don't bend like they used to...so getting in and out of the shower might be difficult. You'd prefer a gas rather than an electric cooktop. You'd rather have something with more personality - high ceilings and french doors...This is in a tower block built in about 1980.
transit: Getting around is really easy once you've got your Opal card and done a little homework on the buses.  They go every few minutes along Oxford St, 7 mins away. The flat is between the city and eastern beaches of Bondi, Bronte, Coogee etc.  Our street sits between two main transport corridors - Oxford St and Anzac Parade with frequent 24hr buses in both directions.  Try the Trip Planner at the Transport NSW site.  It will suggest ways, and how long it takes, and how much it costs, to get to your place of work/family/interest.  Highly recommended before you make a decision.  From the city, catch a 333, 380, (from Circular Quay to Bondi Beach via Bondi Junction) M40 (from Chatswood and North Sydney to Bondi Junction) or 440 (from Central Station to Bronte via Bondi Junction) to the corner of Oxford St and Jersey Rd, Woollahra/Paddington - it's a 7 min walk from there.  These buses are very frequent - all but the M40 run until midnight.  The 380 is 24hrs.  Less frequent daytime buses also r
access: The flat is self contained and you would not be sharing with anyone.
interaction: We'll only lease this place when we go away so unless our departure and your arrival are simultaneous, we'll have to leave you in the hands of a proxy host.
house_rules: - This is our home so please respect our things and always consider how your behaviour might affect neighbours.
host_about:
The Annexe is a place I'd love if I were away from home.   When on the road, location and safe, independent transport is always my priority. Wifi and a laundry make things easy.  I like uncluttered, light spaces and prefer simplicity and informality over anything fancy or fussy.  The Annexe is all these things so please consider...

I've worked as a teacher or sailor in The UK, Spain, Taiwan, Ecuador and Antigua and travelled a great deal in between.  Now working and settled in Sydney with my non travelling partner.  We've been offering short term leases on The Annexe (our investment property) for 6yrs through other sources.  We live in the same street so feel it brings the world to us, with its revolving door of custodians.  

I used Airbnb for the first time as a guest in Melbourne for my Scottish cousin and I in January 2013.  We loved our groovy warehouse there.  Then in July 2014 my mother and I hit the jackpot again with a lovely sunny winter home away from home in Byron Bay.  So I'm a repeat offender, enjoying the Airbnb community as both a host and a guest.

neighborhood_overview: Rich with history, culture and sophistication, Potts Point is an ideal place to stay or visit for those who want to enjoy the picturesque surroundings of a bygone era and still be close to everything Sydney has to offer. Potts Point situated within Sydney City is just a short 20-minute walk to the CBD and a stone's throw from Kings Cross Railway Station, so you can easily catch a train to some of Sydney's major attractions. Sydney Buses, Taxis and Car Hire are also readily available in the immediate vicinity. As for dining out, Victoria St, and in particular Macleay St, are dotted with a range of restaurants to suit all tastes. Kings Cross, Darlinghurst Rd offers a countless number of nightclubs, bars and theatres for those who enjoy the nightlife. Or for the more subdued there are plenty of parks, museums and harbour side charm in the neighbouring suburbs.
notes: Most things you need are in the places you expect to find them.
transit: Plenty of public transport is just outside the door, but walking to the city is even easier than the one or two stops on the train.
access: Guests have access to everything shown in the images. Centennial Park is very close by, hire a bike or stroll around to look at the beautiful gardens or the bird life.

neighborhood_overview: Ticking all the right boxes! Being situated in a very central location saves you valuable time and money.  This place really is a unique opportunity to live like a Sydney-sider. Spring is the perfect time to visit Sydney and the city is the place to be. With festivals and shows popping up all over the city including Hyde Park and the Rocks and with weekend markets just a short walk into Surry Hills and Paddington, this place is perfected located for discovering Sydney. Mrs Maquiarie's Chair is a lovely 5km round trip (40min walk) and the Sydney Opera House is only a 30min walk through the city. host_about:
I'm a self employed company director. I was born in Sydney and have lived here all my life. I know Sydney like the back of my hand and I'm eager to share my local knowledge of the beautiful places & secret gems Sydney has to offer. I work at the building as the building maintenance manager & I'm around at least half of the time to easily assist you in any way I can. I'm also easily contactable at all other times and I'll ensure I make your stay awesome & memorable.
As a host, I'm always trying to improve and better myself. Every interaction with every guest adds to my experiences as a host & improves my ability to understand and service all of your needs. I love sharing information, life experiences, skills & knowledge and in turn I love to learn from others, hearing new ideas and trying new things. I'm a genuine person, I'm accepting of everyone's unique qualities and differences without any pre-judgement or criticism no matter what it is. I love meeting new people & spending time with family & friends. I enjoy all sports, running on the beach, Surfing, listing to music, going to concerts and movies, travelling and everything else life has to offer. 
I once played competitive sports and with a love for the outdoors I chose to study construction rather than a career that would confine me to an office chair. I also hold an associate diploma in applied science and have traveled extensively throughout Europe, North America & parts of South East Asia. Unfortunately, time & money constraints have prevented more recent travel, although I look forward to travelling more in the near future.

host_about:
We are long time Airbnb hosts in Paris and now live in a beautiful inner Sydney apartment in the CBD and very accessible to public transport or simply walk.

Your bright  and airy private room has its private bathroom with bath & toilet, an access to the balcony,  a TV with 28 channels and a big dressing and a view on the bay. All linen, towels, - everything you would expect in a hotel but much, much more space at a quarter of the price.

You are very welcome to use the entire apartment, the kitchen, laundry, lounge... everywhere!

We work during the day and sometimes go out at night but I am sure our paths will cross. We are quiet and very respectful of your space.

The location is perfect for the travelers or business men wanting quick and easy access to everything. 

We are a very short walk to supermarkets, cafes, restaurants and a similarly short walk to all that Surry Hills (famous for its shopping, restaurants, bars and pubs), CBD, Circular Quay (Sydney Opera) and then Darling Harbour have to offer.

Buses to the beach are a block away, light rail is at 2 minute which will take you out of the city. You have several parks around. Its a beautiful neighborhood.
